item.description:
When using the DOM directly, if you have the element reference to an &lt;INPUT&gt; object, you can reference its parent via el.form. However, in ExtJs, there is no such accessor for the form of field. The following ExtJs override adds the getForm() method to a field which will search upward through the ExtDOM until it finds a parent form, or hits a recursion depth of 10.
Example usage:
// Example useage var myField = Ext.
